{
  "texts": [
    "One approach is to explicitly inject assertion knowledge into the model via domain-adaptive pre-training.",
    "A3Test [5] demonstrates this by pre-training on over 188,000 method-assertion pairs using a masked language modeling objective, significantly reducing the 26.71% assertion error rate observed in its predecessor, AthenaTest.",
    "A second strategy leverages external mechanisms to construct pseudo-oracles, with differential testing being the most common method.",
    "For example, JSONTestGen [174] successfully identified 34 real-world bugs by comparing the outputs of multiple versions of the fastjson library on the same inputs.",
    "A third, innovative approach is to outsource complex reasoning to deterministic external tools."
  ]
}